[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Application data development
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document covers the Development of Application Data phase for the railway
control and protection system identified below. It is prepared in accordance
with EN 50716:2023, Clause 8 (Development of application data: systems
configured by application data), and collects eleven output deliverables from
Table A.1:

  28. Application Requirements Specification
  29. Application Preparation Plan
  30. Application Test Specification
  31. Application Architecture and Design
  32. Application Preparation Verification Report
  33. Application Test Report
  34. Source Code of Application Data
  35. Application Data Verification Report
  36. Application Integration Test Specification
  37. Application Integration Test Report
  38. Application Release Note

"Application data" refers to site-specific configuration data (geographic
topology, routing logic, parameter tables) prepared in a domain-specific
language (DSL) or tabular form and compiled for the generic software platform
identified below. This document covers both the specification and execution
result sides of documents 30/33 (Application Test Specification / Report) and
36/37 (Application Integration Test Specification / Report).

BASIC and SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields are taken from EN 50716:2023:
- Table A.1 (docs 28, 30, 33, 34, 36, 37, 38): BASIC=HR, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.1 (docs 29, 31, 35):                 BASIC=R,  SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.1 (doc 32):                           BASIC=--, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.11 (data preparation techniques, Clause 8.4):
    Tabular specification methods: BASIC=R,  SIL_1–4=R.
    Domain specific language:      BASIC=R,  SIL_1–4=R.
    Simulation:                    BASIC=R,  SIL_1=HR, SIL_2=HR, SIL_3=HR, SIL_4=HR.
    Functional testing:            BASIC=M,  SIL_1=M,  SIL_2=M,  SIL_3=M,  SIL_4=M.
    Checklists:                    BASIC=R,  SIL_1=HR, SIL_2=HR, SIL_3=M,  SIL_4=M.
    Fagan inspection:              BASIC=--, SIL_1=R,  SIL_2=R,  SIL_3=R,  SIL_4=R.
    Formal design reviews:         BASIC=R,  SIL_1=HR, SIL_2=HR, SIL_3=HR, SIL_4=HR.
    Formal proof of correctness:   BASIC=--, SIL_1=--, SIL_2=--, SIL_3=HR, SIL_4=HR.
    Walkthrough:                   BASIC=R,  SIL_1=R,  SIL_2=R,  SIL_3=HR, SIL_4=HR.

ATR-xxx are executed application test cases. Both the test specification and
execution results are recorded in each ATR entry.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: APP-xxx (requirements), ATR-xxx (test cases).
- Duplicate ATR entries for each executed test case.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

