[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Application functional requirements

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: APP-020
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Application functional requirements
STATEMENT: >>>
The application data shall implement the signalling functionality described in
the signalling principles document for the installation scope defined in APP-010.

Functional requirements:

  APP-F-001: The application data shall correctly represent the track topology
    (points, signals, track circuits) as defined in the geographic survey.
    Derivation: <geographic survey ref>, sections <x>–<y>.

  APP-F-002: The application data shall implement all routes defined in the
    route register, including entry signal, route elements, destination signal,
    and all locking conditions.
    Derivation: <signalling principles ref>, route register.

  APP-F-003: The application data shall correctly implement approach locking
    and approach release logic for all <n> approach-locked routes.
    Derivation: <signalling principles ref>, section <x>.

  APP-F-004: The application data shall define flank and trap protection
    conditions for all routes as specified in the signalling principles.
    Derivation: <signalling principles ref>, section <x>.

  APP-F-005: The application data shall implement all interface conditions with
    adjacent systems (IF-EXT-01 to IF-EXT-<n>) as defined in the ICD.
    Derivation: <interface control document ref>.

  APP-F-006: The application data parameter values (timing values, speed limits)
    shall be within the ranges defined by the generic software platform
    specification.
    Derivation: <generic SW platform spec ref>, section <x>.

Requirements summary:
  Total application functional requirements: <n>
  Derived from geographic survey:            <n>
  Derived from signalling principles:        <n>
  Derived from interface control document:   <n>
  Derived from platform specification:       <n>
<<<
