[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Application data constraints

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: APP-030
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Application data constraints
STATEMENT: >>>
Application data shall comply with the following constraints imposed by the
generic software platform, safety requirements, and operational considerations.

Data integrity constraints:
  APP-C-001: All element identifiers (signals, points, track circuits) shall
    be unique within the application data set; duplicate identifiers are not
    permitted.
  APP-C-002: All routes shall have a valid entry signal, at least one route
    element, and a valid destination signal, all of which exist in the element
    register.
  APP-C-003: No circular dependencies shall exist in route locking conditions.

Parameter range constraints:
  APP-C-004: All timing parameter values shall lie within the ranges defined
    in the generic software platform specification (see APP-010).
  APP-C-005: Speed limit values shall not exceed the infrastructure maximum
    speed as specified in the geographic survey.
  APP-C-006: Gradient values shall be within <min>‰ to <max>‰ as constrained
    by the platform model.

Consistency constraints:
  APP-C-007: Every element referenced in a route definition shall appear in
    the element register; dangling references are not permitted.
  APP-C-008: Interface element states defined in the application data shall be
    consistent with the signal aspect table in the platform specification.
  APP-C-009: Approach locking distances shall be consistent with the line speed
    and stopping distance model in the signalling principles.

The data preparation tool (<tool name, version>) shall enforce constraints
APP-C-001 through APP-C-009 at compile time. Any constraint violation shall
cause a compilation error and prevent generation of the application data binary.
<<<
