This section constitutes the Application Preparation Plan as required by
EN 50716:2023, Clause 8 and Table A.1 (document 29). It defines the process,
tools, and techniques used during application data development, covering
preparation, verification, testing, and integration of the application data set.
<<<

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Application development process

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: APP-040
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Application data development process
STATEMENT: >>>
Application data development follows the process defined below, in accordance
with EN 50716:2023, Clause 8 and the project SQAP.

Development phases:

  Phase 1 — Requirements capture:
    Input:  Geographic survey, signalling principles, interface control document.
    Output: Application Requirements Specification (APP-010 to APP-030, §2).
    Entry criterion: All source data baselined and reviewed.
    Exit criterion:  Requirements specification reviewed and approved.

  Phase 2 — Application data design:
    Input:  Application Requirements Specification, platform data dictionary.
    Output: Application Architecture and Design (APP-070, APP-080, §4).
    Exit criterion:  Design reviewed per APP-090 (preparation verification).

  Phase 3 — Application data preparation (source coding):
    Input:  Approved architecture and design.
    Output: Source code of application data in <DSL name> (APP-130, §9).
    Exit criterion:  Source files reviewed; compilation successful with zero
                     errors and warnings.

  Phase 4 — Application testing:
    Input:  Compiled application data, generic software platform.
    Output: Application Test Report (ATR-001 series, §6).
    Exit criterion:  All ATR test cases PASS; all PRs closed.

  Phase 5 — Application data verification:
    Input:  Source code, test report, design documentation.
    Output: Application Data Verification Report (APP-110, §7).
    Exit criterion:  Verification verdict: Approved.

  Phase 6 — Application integration testing:
    Input:  Verified application data, full system environment.
    Output: Application Integration Test Report (ATR-101 series, §8).
    Exit criterion:  All integration ATR test cases PASS; all PRs closed.

  Phase 7 — Release:
    Input:  Approved integration test report.
    Output: Application Release Note (APP-140, APP-150, §10).

Roles and responsibilities:
  Application Data Preparer:  <Name, Organisation>
  Application Data Verifier:  <Name, Organisation — independent of preparer>
  Application Data Validator: <Name, Organisation — as applicable per SIL>
  Project Manager:            <Name>

Configuration management: application data source files under version control
in <VCS system>; baseline tags per APP-130.
Change control: changes after Phase 3 freeze require formal change impact
assessment and regression testing per SP-060.
<<<
