[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Application data structure and organisation

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: APP-070
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Application data structure and organisation
STATEMENT: >>>
The application data for <installation scope> is structured into the following
modules, each implemented as a separate source file in <DSL name>:

Application data modules:

  Module name           | Content                                 | File(s)
  ----------------------|-----------------------------------------|-------------------
  Element register      | All track elements with identifiers     | <elements.dsl>
  Route register        | Route definitions and locking logic     | <routes.dsl>
  Interface register    | External system interface conditions    | <interfaces.dsl>
  Parameter table       | Timing values, speed limits, gradients  | <parameters.dsl>
  Topology table        | Track topology and connectivity         | <topology.dsl>
  <Aspect table>        | Signal aspect definitions               | <aspects.dsl>

Inter-module dependencies:

  Route register    → Element register: all elements referenced in routes must
                       be declared in the element register.
  Interface register → Element register: interface elements must be declared.
  Parameter table:   no dependencies on other modules (standalone).
  Topology table    → Element register: topology nodes reference element IDs.

Data dictionary: all data item types, fields, and value ranges are defined
in the platform data dictionary (<document ID, revision>). The application
data shall use only data item types and field names defined therein.

Module sizing (estimated):

  Module            | Items (estimated) | Lines of source (est.)
  ------------------|-------------------|-----------------------
  Element register  | <n>               | <n>
  Route register    | <n>               | <n>
  Interface register| <n>               | <n>
  Parameter table   | <n>               | <n>
  Topology table    | <n>               | <n>
  TOTAL             | <n>               | <n>
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Review
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 8 and Table A.1, doc 31 – Application Architecture and Design.

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Data preparation methodology

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: APP-080
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Application data preparation methodology
STATEMENT: >>>
Application data source files are prepared in <DSL name> in accordance with
the platform data dictionary and the constraints defined in APP-030.

Preparation workflow:

  1. Import geographic survey data: <survey data file, version> imported into
     <DSL editor> to create initial element and topology tables.
  2. Author route definitions: signalling principles route register transcribed
     into the route module using <DSL name> syntax; locking conditions coded
     from the signalling principles document.
  3. Define interface conditions: external system interface conditions coded
     from the interface control document.
  4. Set parameter values: timing values, speed limits, and gradients entered
     from the approved source data; each value traceable to source document
     and section.
  5. Compile: <application compiler> run on all source modules; compilation
     shall complete with zero errors and zero warnings.
  6. Validate: <data validator> run on compiled output; all constraint checks
     (APP-C-001 through APP-C-009) shall pass.

Simulation (Table A.11):
  All functional requirements (APP-020 series) shall be simulated in
  <simulation environment> before formal testing (ATR-xxx). Simulation
  results are recorded in the simulation log (<document ID or tool output>).
  Simulation coverage: all routes exercised in both normal and degraded
  operating modes.

Traceability from source data to compiled output:
  The application compiler generates a traceability report (<output file>)
  mapping each DSL source item to its compiled binary representation.
  Traceability chain: source requirement → DSL source item → compiled data
  element → ATR test case.

Compiler output artefacts:
  Application data binary:  <filename.adb>, SHA-256: <hash>
  Traceability report:      <filename.rpt>
  Compilation log:          <filename.log> (zero errors, zero warnings)
  Validation report:        <filename.vld> (all constraint checks PASS)
<<<
