<<<

[TEST_CASE]
UID: ATR-001
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <Route ID>: nominal route setting and clearance
TEST_TYPE: Validation
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Generic software platform <version> loaded with compiled application data
  <APP-BL-xxx> on <test environment>.
- All track elements in normal state: points normal, signals at danger,
  track circuits clear.
- No conflicting route set or locked.
- All external interfaces (IF-EXT-01 to IF-EXT-<n>) in nominal state.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Issue route-setting command for <Route ID> from entry signal <S-n> to
   destination signal <S-m>.
2. Observe element responses: verify points, flank protection, and trap
   protection elements move to correct positions for <Route ID>.
3. Verify entry signal <S-n> clears to <aspect> and destination signal
   <S-m> remains at danger.
4. Simulate train movement: set track circuits occupied in sequence along
   <Route ID>; verify signals step through correct aspect sequence.
5. Train clears destination track circuit; verify route released and all
   elements return to normal state.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Step 2: all <n> route elements assume correct position per route table.
          All flank and trap protection elements set per APP-F-004.
- Step 3: entry signal <S-n> displays <aspect>; destination <S-m> at danger.
- Step 4: signal aspects step correctly as train occupies each track circuit.
          No unexpected locking or route cancellation.
- Step 5: route released; all elements return to normal within <n> s.
          Trailing route protection (if defined) set correctly.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- Step 2: all <n> route elements: correct positions confirmed. PASS.
          Flank protection elements: correct state confirmed. PASS.
          Trap protection elements: correct state confirmed. PASS.
- Step 3: <S-n> displaying <aspect>. PASS.  <S-m> at danger. PASS.
- Step 4: signal aspect sequence confirmed through <n> track circuit
          occupancies. No unexpected locking or cancellation detected. PASS.
- Step 5: route released after <measured_time> s (limit: <n> s). PASS.
          All elements returned to normal state. PASS.
All APP-F-001, APP-F-002, APP-F-004 criteria met for <Route ID>. PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: APP-020
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: ATR-002
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <Route ID> / <Conflicting Route ID>: conflicting route rejection
TEST_TYPE: Validation
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Generic software platform <version> loaded with compiled application data
  <APP-BL-xxx> on <test environment>.
- <Route ID> set and locked; entry signal <S-n> cleared.
- Track circuits along <Route ID> clear (route locked but not occupied).
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Issue route-setting command for <Conflicting Route ID> which shares
   track element <E-k> with the locked <Route ID>.
2. Observe response: verify that <Conflicting Route ID> is rejected.
3. Verify <Route ID> remains set, locked, and undisturbed.
4. Cancel <Route ID>; confirm route cancellation procedure applies.
5. Issue route-setting command for <Conflicting Route ID> again after
   <Route ID> fully cancelled and all elements normalised.
6. Verify <Conflicting Route ID> sets successfully.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Step 2: route-setting command for <Conflicting Route ID> rejected;
          error code <ERR-CONFLICT> or equivalent returned.
          No elements move to positions for <Conflicting Route ID>.
- Step 3: <Route ID> remains set and locked; signal state unchanged.
- Step 4: route cancellation proceeds per signalling principles timing.
- Step 6: <Conflicting Route ID> sets successfully; all elements and signal
          <S-p> assume correct positions and aspects.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- Step 2: route-setting rejected; code <ERR-CONFLICT> returned. PASS.
          No element movement for <Conflicting Route ID> observed. PASS.
- Step 3: <Route ID> locked and undisturbed; <S-n> still showing <aspect>.
          PASS.
- Step 4: route cancellation complete after <n> s per approach locking timeout.
          All elements normalised. PASS.
- Step 6: <Conflicting Route ID> set successfully; all <n> elements in correct
          positions. <S-p> displaying <aspect>. PASS.
Conflict detection correctly enforced per APP-C-002 and APP-F-002. PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
