[TEST_CASE]
UID: ATR-101
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <Adjacent system> interface: nominal data exchange and aspect propagation
TEST_TYPE: Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Generic software platform <version> loaded with application data <APP-BL-xxx>
  on target hardware.
- Adjacent system <system name> (IF-EXT-01) connected via <communication link>.
- All elements in normal state; no active faults.
- Communication link IF-EXT-01: IN-SERVICE confirmed on both sides.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Verify communication link IF-EXT-01 is established; confirm IN-SERVICE
   status in system diagnostics.
2. Trigger a state change on adjacent system: set <boundary element> to
   occupied state.
3. Observe propagation in the application data: verify <local element>
   assumes correct state per APP-F-005.
4. Issue a route-setting command that depends on <boundary element> state.
5. Verify signal aspects on both sides of the interface respond correctly.
6. Restore <boundary element> to clear state; verify normalisation.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Step 1: IF-EXT-01 IN-SERVICE within <n> s of system start-up.
- Step 3: <local element> state change propagated within <n> ms of adjacent
          system state change (APP-F-005).
- Step 4: route-setting proceeds / rejected as appropriate for current
          <boundary element> state per signalling principles.
- Step 5: signal aspects on both systems consistent with route state.
- Step 6: <local element> returns to normal; no residual fault log entries.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- Step 1: IF-EXT-01 IN-SERVICE confirmed at <measured_time> s. PASS.
- Step 3: <local element> state change at <measured_latency> ms
          (limit: <n> ms). WITHIN LIMIT. PASS.
- Step 4: route setting <proceeded / rejected> correctly per signalling
          principles. PASS.
- Step 5: signal aspects: <observed aspects> (expected: <expected aspects>).
          Consistent across boundary. PASS.
- Step 6: <local element> normalised; 0 fault log entries. PASS.
Interface behaviour correct per APP-F-005 and ICD. Propagation timing confirmed.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: APP-020
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: ATR-102
STATUS: Active
TITLE: Loss of <adjacent system> interface: degraded operation and recovery
TEST_TYPE: Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Generic software platform <version> loaded with application data <APP-BL-xxx>
  on target hardware.
- Adjacent system <system name> (IF-EXT-01) connected and IN-SERVICE.
- All elements in normal state; a route crossing boundary IF-EXT-01 is set.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Disconnect communication link IF-EXT-01 at the network layer.
2. Measure elapsed time to loss-of-communication detection.
3. Observe system response: record element states, signal aspects, and fault
   log entries.
4. Attempt to set a new route crossing IF-EXT-01 while the link is lost.
5. Restore communication link IF-EXT-01; observe recovery sequence.
6. Verify state resynchronisation with adjacent system after link recovery.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Step 2: loss-of-communication detected within <n> ms (APP-F-005).
- Step 3: all elements on <boundary interface> assume fail-safe state; entry
          signals at danger; fault code <FC-LOC-xx> logged.
- Step 4: route-setting command for boundary-crossing route rejected; code
          <ERR-INTERFACE-LOST> or equivalent returned.
- Step 5: link recovery acknowledged; resynchronisation sequence initiated.
- Step 6: element states resynchronised within <n> s; fault code cleared;
          normal operation resumes.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- Step 2: loss-of-communication detected at <measured_time> ms
          (limit: <n> ms). WITHIN LIMIT. PASS.
- Step 3: boundary elements: fail-safe state confirmed. PASS.
          Signals at danger confirmed. PASS.
          Fault log: code <FC-LOC-xx>, timestamp <HH:MM:SS.mmm>. PASS.
- Step 4: route-setting rejected; code <ERR-INTERFACE-LOST> returned. PASS.
- Step 5: link recovery sequence initiated at <timestamp>. PASS.
- Step 6: resynchronisation complete at <measured_time> s (limit: <n> s).
          Fault code cleared. Normal operation confirmed. PASS.
Degraded operation and recovery behaviour correct per APP-F-005. PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: APP-020
  ROLE: Verifies

